  "text": "## Envoy Dynamic Cluster Discovery and Health Checking Implementation\n\n### Overview\nThe Envoy proxy implements dynamic cluster discovery and health checking through a coordinated system of C++ components spanning multiple subsystems. The implementation consists of four main areas:\n\n### 1. CDS (Cluster Discovery Service) - Dynamic Cluster Subscription\n\n**CDS API Implementation:**\n- `source/common/upstream/cds_api_impl.cc` and `cds_api_impl.h` implement the main CDS API that subscribes to cluster updates via gRPC. The `CdsApiImpl` class inherits from both `CdsApi` and `SubscriptionBase<envoy::config::cluster::v3::Cluster>`, managing cluster subscriptions through the `onConfigUpdate` method.\n- `source/common/upstream/cds_api_helper.cc` and `cds_api_helper.h` provide helper utilities for managing cluster additions and updates during CDS configuration changes.\n\n**On-Demand CDS (ODCDS):**\n- `source/common/upstream/od_cds_api_impl.cc` and `od_cds_api_impl.h` implement on-demand cluster discovery, allowing dynamic cluster discovery for clusters not known at startup. The `OdCdsApiImpl` class extends `SubscriptionBase<envoy::config::cluster::v3::Cluster>` and manages pending cluster requests through `requestOnDemandClusterDiscovery`.\n- `source/common/upstream/cluster_discovery_manager.cc` and `cluster_discovery_manager.h` manage the lifecycle of on-demand cluster discovery requests, tracking pending cluster discovery callbacks.\n\n### 2. Cluster Manager Update Logic - Configuration and Lifecycle\n\n**Cluster Manager Implementation:**\n- `source/common/upstream/cluster_manager_impl.cc` and `cluster_manager_impl.h` implement the core `ClusterManagerImpl` that orchestrates cluster lifecycle management. This file contains critical methods like `addOrUpdateCluster`, `checkActiveStaticCluster`, and cluster update callbacks. The manager initializes CDS through `ClusterManagerInitHelper::setCds`.\n- `source/common/upstream/cluster_factory_impl.cc` and `cluster_factory_impl.h` implement the `ClusterFactoryImplBase` that creates cluster instances based on configuration types.\n\n**Cluster Implementation:**\n- `source/common/upstream/upstream_impl.cc` and `upstream_impl.h` implement `ClusterImplBase` and related cluster infrastructure classes. The `finishInitialization` method (line 1674) completes cluster initialization after EDS/health check setup.\n- `source/extensions/clusters/eds/eds.cc` and `eds.h` implement `EdsClusterImpl`, the endpoint discovery service cluster handler. The `onConfigUpdate` method (line 182) processes endpoint updates from EDS subscriptions. The `reloadHealthyHostsHelper` method (line 356) integrates health check results with EDS updates.\n- `source/extensions/clusters/eds/leds.cc` and `leds.h` implement locality-based endpoint discovery with `LedsSubscription` managing locality-specific endpoint updates.\n\n### 3. Active Health Check Scheduling\n\n**Health Checker Implementation:**\n- `source/common/upstream/health_checker_impl.cc` and `health_checker_impl.h` implement `HealthCheckerFactory::create` (line 50) that instantiates appropriate health checkers based on configuration. This is the entry point for health check initialization.\n- `source/extensions/health_checkers/common/health_checker_base_impl.cc` and `health_checker_base_impl.h` implement `HealthCheckerImplBase`, the base class for all health checkers. Contains timer management with `interval_timer_` (line 88) and `timeout_timer_` (line 89) for scheduling health checks.\n\n**Protocol-Specific Health Checkers:**\n- `source/extensions/health_checkers/http/health_checker_impl.cc` and `health_checker_impl.h` implement HTTP health checking protocol.\n- `source/extensions/health_checkers/redis/redis.cc` and `config.cc` implement Redis health checking.\n- `source/extensions/health_checkers/thrift/client_impl.cc` and `config.cc` implement Thrift health checking.\n\n**Health Discovery Service:**\n- `source/common/upstream/health_discovery_service.cc` and `health_discovery_service.h` implement `HdsDelegate` for health discovery service, managing cluster health check configuration updates through `updateHdsCluster` (line 199).\n\n### 4. Outlier Detection Integration\n\n**Outlier Detection Implementation:**\n- `source/common/upstream/outlier_detection_impl.cc` and `outlier_detection_impl.h` implement `DetectorImpl` and `DetectorImplFactory`. The factory's `create` method (line 377) instantiates outlier detection for clusters with the configuration. `DetectorImpl` monitors host failure patterns and ejects unhealthy hosts.\n\n### 5. Configuration Subscription and gRPC Transport\n\n**gRPC Mux and Subscription:**\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_mux_impl.cc` and `grpc_mux_impl.h` implement `GrpcMuxImpl`, the core gRPC multiplexer managing simultaneous subscriptions (CDS, EDS, etc.) over a single gRPC stream. The `addWatch` method enables subscription management.\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/watch_map.cc` and `watch_map.h` implement `WatchMap`, managing multiple watches for different resource types. The `onConfigUpdate` method (line 36) distributes configuration updates to interested subscribers.\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/grpc_subscription_impl.cc` and `grpc_subscription_impl.h` implement subscription mechanics.\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/delta_subscription_state.cc` and `delta_subscription_state.h` manage incremental (delta) xDS subscription state.\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/new_grpc_mux_impl.cc` and `new_grpc_mux_impl.h` provide an alternative gRPC mux implementation.\n- `source/extensions/config_subscription/grpc/eds_resources_cache_impl.cc` and `eds_resources_cache_impl.h` cache EDS resources for efficient reuse.\n\n### 6. On-Demand Filter Integration\n\n**On-Demand Request Handling:**\n- `source/extensions/filters/http/on_demand/on_demand_update.cc` implements on-demand cluster discovery in HTTP filters. The `handleOnDemandCds` method (line 134) initiates cluster discovery requests and callbacks.\n- `source/common/tcp_proxy/tcp_proxy.cc` implements TCP proxy filter with cluster discovery support through `onClusterDiscoveryCompletion` (line 519).\n\n### Data Flow Summary\n\nThe complete data flow for dynamic cluster discovery and health checking:\n\n1. **Initialization**: ClusterManagerImpl creates CdsApiImpl which starts subscription\n2. **Cluster Updates**: GrpcMuxImpl receives cluster updates, WatchMap distributes to CdsApiImpl.onConfigUpdate\n3. **Cluster Creation**: ClusterManagerImpl.addOrUpdateCluster creates cluster via ClusterFactoryImpl\n4. **Health Check Setup**: ClusterImplBase.finishInitialization creates health checkers via HealthCheckerFactory\n5. **Health Check Scheduling**: HealthCheckerImplBase manages interval_timer_ for periodic checks\n6. **Endpoint Updates**: EdsClusterImpl.onConfigUpdate processes EDS updates and integrates with health check results\n7. **Outlier Detection**: DetectorImpl monitors failures and triggers ejections via callbacks\n8. **On-Demand Discovery**: OdCdsApiImpl handles dynamic cluster discovery requests from filters\n\nThis architecture enables Envoy to dynamically discover and manage clusters, continuously monitor their health, and automatically eject failing endpoints while respecting outlier detection policies."
}

